  "text": [
    "Some little splinter",
    "Of shadow purls",
    "And weals down",
    "The slewed stone",
    "Chapel steps,",
    "Slinks along",
    "The riverrock wall",
    "And disappears",
    "Into the light.",
    "Now ropy, riffled,",
    "Now owlish, sere,",
    "It smolders back",
    "To sight beneath",
    "A dwarfish, brindled tree",
    "That chimes and sifts",
    "And resurrects",
    "In something\u2019s sweet",
    "And lethal breath.",
    "This little shadow",
    "Seems to know",
    "(How can it know?",
    "How can it not?)",
    "Just when to flinch",
    "Just where to loop and sag",
    "And skitter down,",
    "Just what to squirrel",
    "And what to squander till",
    "The light it lacks",
    "Bleeds it back",
    "And finds",
    "My sleeping dark-haired girl \u2014",
    "O personal,",
    "Impersonal,",
    "Continual thrall \u2014",
    "And hammocks blue",
    "In the hollows of her eyes."
  ],
  "title": "I Looked for Life and Did a Shadow See",
  "year": ""
}